ROKUScientific Name Ursus RokustusCommon Name Roku BearDescription Roku Bear is a mediumsized bear native to North America It is the continents smallest and most backward bear species Unlike its cousins TSLA Bear Ursus Teslanus and NVDA Bear Ursus Nividianus which are fearsome hunters and predators Roku Bear relies on scavenging on litters and trash bins TSLA bears and NVDA bears are able to adapt and prosper by preying on weak preys Roku bear due to its limited brain evolution cannot detect weak preys Most of the time they charge on larger prey much bigger than their own size and end up getting their ass kicked So thats why nowadays we can find them hang around trash dumping area scavenging for foodSPY QQQ
